==English==
===Etymology===
Greek '''[[Ναζαρηνός]]''' ''(Nazarēnos),'' an [[ethnonym]] of '''[[Ναζαρέθ]]''' ''(Nazareth).''  For a list of theories as to the further etymology of this word, please consult the [[w:Nazarene|Wikipedia article on ‘Nazarene’]].

===Adjective===
'''Nazarene'''
# Of or pertaining to [[Nazareth]] or its people.
# {{rfv-sense}} Of, from, or pertaining to Nazara, the Nazarene community or the Nazarene dialect.

===Proper noun===
'''Nazarene'''

# A person from [[Nazareth]].
# ''([[kat' exochen|κατ' ἐξωχήν]])'' [[Jesus Christ]].
# {{rfv-sense}} A person from [[Nazar]] or of Nazarene descent.

